  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dd4\u0d9b \u0d86\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dab\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0da7 \u0d86\u0db4\u0dc4\u0dd4 \u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 - WHO \u0d89\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dcf \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd3",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Go back to face masks - WHO urges",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "With the global rise in Covid-19 cases, WHO Director-General Dr. Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus urged authorities to resume wearing masks, staying in well-ventilated areas and maintaining social distancing.",
        "Speaking at the weekly briefing, Tedros said, \"The virus is running free. It appears that countries are not managing the disease effectively.\" Namely.",
        "With the World Health Organization concluding last week that the virus remains a 'public health emergency of international concern', Tedros said the epidemic was nowhere near an end.",
        "More than 5.7 million new cases of Covid-19 were reported during the week of July 4-10, 2022, an increase of 6% compared to the previous week. However, mortality has remained relatively low throughout this summer."
      ],
